    • Class Math.Display.Calculator.EquationDisplay extends javax.swing.JComponent implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • EQUATION

          java.lang.String EQUATION
          Equation that will be passed to CalcWindow to calculate the result.

        • ISEQIMAG

          boolean ISEQIMAG
          True if the equation's result should be expected to be imaginary. If it is, then the real / imaginary axis will be used instead of the x / y axis.

        • STEPS

          double[] STEPS
          The amount that x (or y as well if ISEQIMAG is true) will be incremented when graphing.

        • EQUATION_BOUNDS

          double[] EQUATION_BOUNDS
          The starting and ending point of x (and y if ISEQIMAG is true).

        • WINDOW_BOUNDS

          int[] WINDOW_BOUNDS
          The physical amount of pixels the window is wise and tall. The array will look like the following: (min X, max X, min Y, max Y)

        • DISPLAY_BOUNDS

          int[] DISPLAY_BOUNDS
          The min and max x/y values used for display. Increasing them incrases the zoom level, and shifting them a certain direction shifts the "window" that direction.

          The array will look like the following: (min X, max X, min Y, max Y).

        • COLOR

          java.awt.Color COLOR
          The color that the graph will be drawn in

        • drawer

          java.awt.Graphics2D drawer
          The element that draws the lines.
